1. Employee Onboarding
Register new employees.
Capture personal, job, and contact details.
Upload and manage required documents.
Generate employee ID.
Assign department, designation, and reporting manager.
2. User Account Management
Automatically create employee system accounts.
Assign roles and access permissions based on job role.
Send login credentials and onboarding instructions.
3. Task Management
Assign onboarding tasks to HR, IT, Finance, and Admin teams.
Track task completion status.
Send reminders for pending tasks.
4. Asset Management
Allocate company assets such as laptops, ID cards, access cards, and software licenses.
Maintain asset allocation records.
5. Notifications
Send email or SMS notifications for:
New employee onboarding
Pending approvals
Document submission
Asset allocation
Exit process updates
6. Employee Dashboard
Display onboarding progress.
View assigned tasks.
Access company policies and required documents.
Update personal information.
7. Offboarding Process
Initiate employee exit request.
Generate exit checklist.
Disable user accounts automatically.
Revoke system access.
Collect company assets.
Process final clearance.
8. Exit Clearance
Obtain approvals from HR, Manager, IT, Finance, and Admin.
Track clearance status.
Generate final settlement records.
9. Reports
Onboarding completion reports.
Offboarding status reports.
Asset allocation reports.
Employee activity reports.
Department-wise onboarding/offboarding statistics.
10. Security and Access Control
Secure user authentication.
Role-based access control (Admin, HR, Manager, Employee, IT).
Audit logs for employee actions and approvals.
Expected Outcomes
Reduced manual HR effort.
Faster onboarding and offboarding processes.
Improved accuracy and compliance.
Better tracking of employee tasks and assets.
Centralized management of employee lifecycle data.
